{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = José María Montes | title = [[Bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Chascomús|Diocese of Chascomús]] [[Emeritus]] | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Chascomús|Diocese of Chascomús]] | term = 1983 - 1996 | predecessor = Rodolfo Bufano | successor = [[Juan Carlos Maccarone]] <!-- Orders --> | ordination = December 20, 1958 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{birth date|1920|3|22}} | birth_place = [[Almirante Brown Partido|Almirante Brown, Argentina]] [[Image:Flag of Argentina.svg|25px]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2011|9|2|1920|3|22}} | death_place = | previous_post = }}
'''José María Montes''' (March 22, 1920 &ndash; September 2, 2011) was an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].
Montes was born in Almirante Brown, Argentina and was ordained a priest on December 20, 1958 from the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of La Plata in Argentina|Archdiocese of La Plata]]. He was appointed Auxiliary Archbishop of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of La Plata in Argentina|Archdiocese of La Plata]] on June 15, 1978 as well as titular bishop of Lamdia, and was ordained bishop on August 15, 1978. Montes was appointed to the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Chascomús|Diocese of Chascomús]] on January 19, 1983, where he served until his retirement on July 3, 1996.
