{{MOS|date=July 2013}} This is a '''list of [[yeshiva]]s, [[midrasha]]s and [[Hebrew school]]s in [[Israel]]''' and the [[West Bank]].
A [[yeshiva]] ([[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]: ישיבה) is a center for the study of [[Torah]], the [[Talmud]], and character development in [[Orthodox Judaism]]. A yeshiva usually is led by a rabbi called a Rosh Yeshiva (Head of the Yeshiva). A midrasha ([[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]: מדרשה) or seminary is an equivalent center for Jewish women.
