{{Infobox book | name = The Occult Roots of Nazism: The Ariosophists of Austria and Germany, 1890-1935 | image = File:The Occult Roots of Nazism (first edition).jpg | caption = Cover of the first edition | author = [[Nicholas Goodrick-Clarke]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = English | series = | subject = [[Ariosophy]] | publisher = | pub_date = 1985 | media_type = Print | pages = | isbn = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''The Occult Roots of Nazism: The Ariosophists of Austria and Germany, 1890-1935''''' is a book about [[Nazi occultism]] and [[Ariosophy]] by historian [[Nicholas Goodrick-Clarke]], who traces some of its roots back to [[Esotericism in Germany and Austria]] between 1880 and 1945. The foreword is by [[Rohan Butler]], who had written ''The Roots of National Socialism'' in the 1930s. The book is based on Goodrick-Clarke's 1982 Ph.D. [[thesis]] ''The ariosophists of Austria and Germany 1890-1935: Reactionary political fantasy in relation to social anxiety''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.scientificcommons.org/31951906 |title=Scientific Commons |publisher=En.scientificcommons.org |date= |accessdate=2012-09-13}}</ref>
This book has been continually in print since its first publication in 1985, and has been translated into twelve languages, including Spanish, French, Polish, Italian, Russian, Czech, German and Greek.<ref>German edition, front jacket</ref> It was republished as a paperback by [[New York University]] Press in 1992 ({{ISBN|0-8147-3060-4}}), and more recently republished by [[I.B. Tauris|I.B. Tauris & Co]] Ltd ({{ISBN|1-86064-973-4}}).
The German edition features a preface and an additional essay ''Nationalsozialismus und Okkultismus'' (''National Socialism and Occultism'') (15 pages) by H.T. Hakl.
